76561198127402574,Recommended,288140,18504921,"Posted: 16 October, 2015",all,Protus,"Well after having played Perfect Golf for a few weeks ( 75 hrs ) now I figured I would give my review of how the game is and stands currently. This game is still in the Pre release stage (10/15) and updating gameplay and features.  I have played all the courses and used the different settings and features.With just a standard mouse $7 cheapo the game plays pretty good and has the overall feel of golfing on the course. You can play 3 Click or with Mouse swing currently. The courses they have so far are really nice and some you will be able to remember seeing before as they are real PGA golf courses. Scoring was not too bad, it does depend on the level you play with and how well you can do with the controls on the system you have. I managed to break par on beginner, but Pro level has still kept me over par.There is a gameroom and multiplayer to find matches. They have also just introduced AI golfers that you can set up to play matches with you as well.  There are several different gameplay options like strokeplay, skins, matchplay, etc.. You can change the weather, wind, stimp of the greens, tees. and other settings to increase difficulty.A Course Designer is coming called The Course Forge that really looks nice.  It does need to be used with Unity to lay out the Base Terrain. After you make your initial terrain you would use the CF to apply the different fairways, greens, bunkers, distances, tees, course objects, etc....If you are looking for a Golf Game that gives you a challenge and feels like playing golf I would say go for it.Perfect Golf will make you think twice about how your are going to play that next shot."
