76561198014359125,Recommended,288140,19304084,"Posted: 27 November, 2015",all,brucemcrae,"To start, this is simply the best golf simulator I've come across. There are times when I enjoy it more than the real thing, simply because I score better.I do, however, have one major complaint, that being the lack of a full range of practice facilities. In the real world I spend much of my golf time practicing the short game; pitching, chipping, putting and sand traps. Unfortunately all one can really do in PG in the way of practice is go to the range.  I do find aspects of the short game hard to adjust to in PG (particularly chipping weight) and would welcome the opportunity to be able to go to a practice green, place my ball wherever I wish, and try different clubs, swing types, etc.I would like to think this is in the works and can appreciate the challenges it may create, however to be ranked a great, if not the greatest golf game, it simply has to be part of the package. Can you imagine arriving at a world class golf resort and discovering there was no practice green. The Horror!"
