76561198207191504,Recommended,288140,21515609,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,heavyswinger,"The key to deciding whether you should buy this game is whether you like golf.  Real life golf is frustrating, but very rewarding if you can achieve success, and to do that, it takes some work.  This game is the same way, you have to put some time in to get some success - but it can be fun on the way due to the high quality courses available upon which to play.  I have been pleasantly surprised by the quailty of the courses, both the ones supplied by default in the game, and the user designed courses which so far have proven to be of as high a quality as the default courses.My favorite method of play (swing type) is the newly implemented Real Time Swing - Motion Swing which is proving to be very immersive giving you the feeling that you are really on a golf course and not sitting in front of a computer.Some of the new courses and swing type changes is stirring more interest in this game and there is quite a community of active players who hang out in the lobby for online multiplayer games.  There is also a site which offers weekly tournaments seemlessly integrated into the game with nearly 100 players signed up at the tour pro level (the one I play).  I do not know how many play in the other level tournaments, I suspect that it is 100s more.  There are currently no additional costs to fully participate in the game, courses, lobby or tournaments (although the tournament host does solicit donations on the website through a button).  Eventually there will be premium content for purchase (licensed courses, and accesories which will only be cosmetic and not give you an advantage in the game), but that content will not be necessary to enjoy the game.There will be a program called course forge which will allow anyone who purchases this game to design beautiful course the same way that the original ones were developed.  The current crop of user developed courses were designed by beta testers of course forge.  Course forge will come out when the game exits Early Access, probably sometime this year (but don't quote me).Pluses - gameplay is rich, not repetitive, due to realistic physics and variabilityinterest in the game is growing, lots of partners/opponents availabledeveloper is active, listens to gamers suggestions and incorporates improvementsgame works on multiple platforms including golf simulatorsMinuses - game requires modern computer graphics power to enjoy smooth gameplayplayers who want instant gratification may be disappointed with learning curveMy advice is to purchase this game while it is still in Early Access as it will surely be more than $20 when it is fully released."
