76561198150891244,Recommended,288140,21437843,"Posted: 24 February, 2016",all,bortimus,"Highly recommended.  A recent update added quite a few community made courses (along with updates to the stock courses in the game) and also added several new swing styles.A wide range of swing styles are available:Traditional 3-click with a power meterMotion Swing with the mouse that has a meter on the screen (your choice of swinging horizontally or vertically)Real Time Swing with the mouse (your choice of swinging horizontally or vertically.  No meter on the screen but the player animation moves in concert with the mouse movement)Real Time Swing with a controllerThe game can also be played on a home golf simulator.The motion swings are my personal favorites.  Tempo has a large part in determining the outcome of the shot (as well as swing path and heel/toe hits)  so it's not as simple as straight back/straight through.  A truly wonderful way to play PC golf.There are also a wide range of difficulty options so you can jump right in and enjoy the game.  The easier levels are a great introduction to the game.  Casual player or just want to have a fun round?  It's here.The highest levels of difficulty are quite tough but it doesn't feel unfair or gimmicky.  If you can control your swing, you can still score well.  If you're not playing well, it can be a real grind, but  it is so rewarding when you put a good swing on the ball.  A great option for the hardcore sim player.The course designs are beautiful and the ball physics are the best I've seen in a PC golf game.  A wide range of stimp settings are available for the green speeds, several firmness settings for the fairways, and several settings for pin positions.Currently there are about 33 courses in the game, as well as a large driving range and a short game practice area.The game is still in Early Access so things are still being worked on.  Things not yet included in the game but are planned for the future:-Career mode-Assortments of clothing/animations/clubheads/balls/shafts etc...-Course building software-More courses-Improved AI for the CPU players-Country clubs and tournamentsThere currently is a REALLY good third party tournament site that hosts weekly tournaments for various skill levels as well as fun ancillary events.They have an automatic scoring system set up that will keep track of your scores and stats after each round and maintains them on their site.  They also maintain different tours, world rankings, money leaders, ongoing season stats, etc.. and it's free to join.  A very well run tour.http://onlinegolftour.net/index.htmlI'm sure I'm forgetting some things but again, this is a great game."
