76561198057828822,Recommended,288140,25212460,"Posted: 28 August, 2016",all,Pompe,"Just wanted to write down a few words about this game now when I´ve been playing a number of rounds.I´ve been playing golfgames since the Commodore 64 time before the first Links-game came out and I also play golf in real life. Not saying that makes my review more credible, but it may give a hint on what I look for and am annoyed with...There´s lots of graphical adjustments to suit most people which is good. You have your sound options and of course your golfer customization. You can pick your clubs and equipment and buy more if thas not enough for you. At the moment you don´t have that much to buy so perhaps thats something that will be added along the way. A bunch of golf courses are included and more are available to buy for a few bucks. I´m fine with that. The courses included are fine and varying in style.You have your practice mode which I think could be better if you had more putting and pitching options and such. Tourmaments are not used much as far as I can see which is a shame. Multiplayer will be your only option if you want to play with other players but my feeling is that this is not very active. You have to work a bit to get a game started. If you just want to play a few holes you´ll probably end up chosing solo-play anyway.I feel I can go on and on about this so I´ll just end with what I think works well and what doesn´t.Graphics are fine even though animations could be alot better.Sound effects are good but the game is really missing commentary. It feel lonely out there too often.Motionswing is frustration and annying - in other words perfect! That´s golf! :) No seriously I feel they´ve done a great job with that one. You need to practice and you won´t get it perfect all the time.Putting is hard which is also fine but I don´t like the fact that you almost all the time have to aim 5 meters to your left/right because the greens have such big slopes. That´s just not very realistic I´m afraid. There´s some work to be done here.As I´m a ""leftie"" I of course miss the left handed player...Would I recommend the game? Well...there aren´t too many good golf games out there today so I guess we can´t be too selective here. If you like to play a quick round now and then and aren´t that interested in career modes and the stuff EA:s Tiger Woods golf had to offer, this game should be enough for you. I wouldn´t pick it up for retail price though as I don´t think the game is finished yet. To me it´s still in ""early access""."
