76561198003825561,Recommended,288140,33061447,Posted: 30 June,all,Daddio,"This isn't easy for me to rate.  First, I think it is quite fun to play a round.  It does bring back the good ol days of pc golf games.  But that said, it is pretty limited.  You have one avatar and limited selection for modifying your player.  There is no season that I can find, and I usually only see one or two games for online play, which doesn't bother me i just play locally anyway, but if that's your thing be warned.  In the end, I enjoy playing single rounds of golf here, but I don't like the lack of depth and customization.  I do, however, like playing around with the course maker and may one day finish a course.  The developers have great tutorials on doing this, which gives me hope for more custom mods for clubs, shafts, grips, gloves, balls, etc...I am recommending,  for the reasons stateds, but realize what you're getting;  the thumbs down reviews are valid here as well."
