76561198200268002,Recommended,288140,24671114,"Posted: 2 August, 2016",all,rseitz1009,"Despite the naysayers, I find this to be a truly great golf sim.  There are free courses of every description available and very many of them are fine renditions of courses both real and imagined, though the game arrives with a worthy selection to begin with.  You can set the time of day and the weather.  The graphics are great -- early morning sunlight is wonderful shining through the trees and creating realistic shadows.  You can set up computer players to challenge you or just play alone if you wish (I like a player to join me).  It seems to me that the swing accuracy is good, although I must admit that when your computer partner sinks putts and chips from all over the place it's a bit discouraging.I don;t know what you might demand of a golf sim, but for my money this is as good as they get, and then some!  So without reservation, I highly recommend this game to any and all who enjoy computer golf.  Get it."
